title: Grateful Dead Live at San Francisco Civic Auditorium on 1984-12-29
lineage: Cassette (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/96k) -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.03 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

One More Saturday Night, Friend Of The Devil, My Brother Esau, Big Railroad Blues, Cassidy, Althea, Let It Grow

Set 2

Samson & Delilah-> Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Stella Blue-> Not Fade Away-> E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: How do I get there from here This is good. It sounds a bit muddy, was there a fetish with Dolby or something. Anyways I have a list of 40 shows mainly 84/85 I wish were here on Archive. In sbd. Thanks to These Walker Scotton people, and Mr. Miller, wherever they are, they uploaded what was, so much of it were my first tens of shows, wishing there were updates, like on 4 21 84 or umm 10/12/84 Augusta which we drove up to and stumbled on in. I was 16, barely. I had eaten through Hendrix, the Doors etc. (The adolescent bands) and was ready for this man yelling in a room with his sidekick AKA The Grateful Dead. This sounds the way 12/28/86 sounds. Would love an update to come Up From The Skies. 3 is cause It doesn't play loud. It is better than it is.

Playing Jam... You could say this would be the best Playing Jam of the year or surrounding years!  Very exploratory indeed, top shelf.
Highlights: Playing In The Band, Drums, Space
